 About Unchained Money                                     
                       
  Unchained Money is your personal debt freedom roadmap. It analyses your income, expenses, loans, and savings to create a step-by-step plan to become
  debt-free — prioritising high-interest debt first to save you maximum interest.                                                                         
   
  What it does:                                                                                                                                           
                                                            
  - Financial Health Score — Calculates your score based on debt-to-income ratio and interest burden                                                      
  - Month-by-month Roadmap — Shows exactly where every unit of your surplus goes, with a live timeline you can track over time
  - Smart Debt Ordering — Prioritises informal debt and credit card outstanding first, then tackles remaining loans by highest interest rate (avalanche   
  method). As each loan clears, its freed EMI snowballs into the next — accelerating payoff                                                               
  - Emergency Fund Building — Builds your safety net alongside debt payoff, with a medical buffer if you lack health insurance                            
  - Smart SIP Management — Pauses your SIP when high-interest debt exists (>10%) and resumes it automatically once cleared                                
  - Excess Savings Optimisation — Optionally uses savings above your emergency fund as a lump-sum payment to accelerate debt payoff                       
  - Lump-Sum Payments — Record one-time payments anytime and see the roadmap recalculate instantly, showing how many months you saved                     
  - Salary Hike Tracking — Log a salary increase and watch your debt-free date move closer as the extra surplus is applied automatically                  
  - Live Timeline — Past lump-sum and hike events appear inline in your roadmap with a "Today" marker showing exactly where you stand                     
  - Balance Check-ins — When you return after a month or more, the app prompts you to update your loan balances so the roadmap stays accurate             
  - Progress Tracking — Motivational milestones as each loan gets cleared                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                          
  How it works — Examples:                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                          
  Example 1: Ravi, salaried professional                                                                                                                  
  Ravi earns ₹75,000/month, spends ₹35,000, and has two loans — a credit card outstanding of ₹2,45,000 at 42% and a personal loan of ₹4,10,000 at 18%.
  Unchained Money identifies his surplus of ₹8,000/month, splits it 50/50 between emergency fund and debt, and directs all extra payments to the 42%      
  credit card first. When the credit card clears in month 14, its ₹8,000 EMI snowballs into the personal loan — clearing all debt by month 28 instead of
  42.                                                                                                                                                     
                                                            
  Example 2: Priya, freelancer with savings                                                                                                               
  Priya has ₹3,00,000 in savings but only needs ₹1,20,000 for her emergency fund. She has a ₹2,00,000 personal loan at 16%. Unchained Money detects the
  ₹1,80,000 excess and offers a toggle — if she opts in, the excess is applied as a lump-sum, reducing her outstanding to just ₹20,000. Her debt-free date
   moves from 22 months to 2 months.                        
                                                                                                                                                          
  Example 3: Ananya, no health insurance                                                                                                                  
  Ananya has no health insurance. Unchained Money adds a medical buffer (2 months extra) to her emergency fund target — raising it from ₹1,50,000 to
  ₹2,50,000. Her roadmap accounts for the higher target, and the insurance warning explains exactly how much she can reduce her EF requirement by getting 
  ₹5,00,000+ cover.                                         
                                                                                                                                                          
  Example 4: Karthik, SIP investor with debt                
  Karthik invests ₹10,000/month in SIPs but also has a ₹3,00,000 personal loan at 15%. Unchained Money pauses his SIP and redirects that ₹10,000 toward
  the loan — because paying off 15% debt saves more than typical 10-12% market returns. Once the loan clears, his SIP resumes automatically and his       
  roadmap shows the exact month it restarts.
                                                                                                                                                          
  Example 5: Meera, returning after 3 months                
  Meera set up her roadmap in January and returns in April. Unchained Money detects the gap and prompts her to update her loan balances. She enters the
  latest amounts, and the roadmap regenerates with accurate projections. Her past lump-sum payment from February appears inline in the timeline, with a   
  "Today" marker showing her current position — so she can see how far she's come and what's ahead.
                                                                                                                                                          
  What it doesn't do:                                                                                                                                     
  - No financial advice — this is an educational planning tool only
  - No data leaves your device — everything is stored locally on your device                                                                              
  - No sign-up, no accounts, no tracking                                    
                                                                                                                                                          
  Works globally, built with India in mind — auto-detects your device currency (₹, $, £, and more), supports Indian number grouping (lakhs/crores), local 
  loan types (gold loans, credit card EMI, loan against property, informal lending), and accounts for PF, gold, and SIP in your financial picture.        
                                                                                                                                                          
  Always consult a certified financial advisor before making major financial decisions. 
